"{\"uid\": \"pennlive.com-entertainment-2024-07-commentator-removed-from-olympic-coverage-for-inappropriate-remark-about-female-swimmers.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"It's an attempt to make things right.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 37, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After making what the audience coined as a sexist remark about Australia's women's swim team, a broadcaster removed from Eurosport's 2024 Summer Olympics coverage is now issuing an apology.\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 102, \"end\": 111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9995344708426159, \"rank\": 0.0004332664673931626, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 160, \"end\": 169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.778226455183782e-15, \"text\": \"Eurosport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Longtime swimming commentator Bob Ballard took to social media on July 29 to address the controversy, sharing that it was \\\"never my intention to upset or belittle anyone.\\\"\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9994664443436956, \"rank\": 0.0002747109727456045, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 264, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999945821356389, \"rank\": 4.819053399833175e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The comments I made during the Australian freestyle relay victory ceremony on Saturday have caused some offense,\\\" the commentatorposted on X, formerly known as Twitter.\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9947757615087005, \"rank\": 0.005126365307424087, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.6374895600046256e-13, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was never my intention to upset or belittle anyone and, if I did, I apologize.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a massive advocate of women's sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He alsoshared, \\\"I shall miss the Eurosport team, dearly and wish them all the best for the rest of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No further comment will be issued.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you.\\\"\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The day before, on July 28, according to multiple media outlets includingDeadlineandThe Independent, Ballard made an inappropriate comment about Australia's women's 4x100m freestyle relay team.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 1054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9995344708426159, \"rank\": 0.0004332664673931626, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Well, the women [are] just finishing up.\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You know what women are like \\u2026 hanging around, you know, doing their makeup.\\\"\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His comment came after the women - Mollie O'Callaghan, Shayna Jack, Emma McKeon and Meg Harris - exited the Paris Aquatic Center after winning a gold medal in the event.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mollie O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shayna Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma McKeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\"}, {\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Meg Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995417307359, \"rank\": 4.5826947912900916e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The comment went viral on social media, sparking outrage.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the comment, fellow commentator Lizzie Simmonds said Ballard's comment was \\\"outrageous.\\\"\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999945821356389, \"rank\": 4.819053399833175e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has yet to publicly further comment.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon after, Eurosport took swift action and dropped Ballard from its coverage.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999945821356389, \"rank\": 4.819053399833175e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A statement was then released to The Independent.\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1675, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"During a segment of Eurosport's coverage last night, commentator Bob Ballard made an inappropriate comment.\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9994664443436956, \"rank\": 0.0002747109727456045, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999945821356389, \"rank\": 4.819053399833175e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To that end, he has been removed from our commentary roster with immediate effect,\\\" the statement read.\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spending more than four decades in media, Ballard has covered swimming, diving, and water polo during his broadcasting career.\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999945821356389, \"rank\": 4.819053399833175e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EmilyAnn Jackman is a trending reporter for Penn Live.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Patriot-News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penn Live\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Patriot-News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Patriot-News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She handles the top trending topics on social media, as well as  breaking stories in pop culture and entertainment news that goes viral on a national...more  Use of and/or registration on any